snippet.textDisplay:
What a beautiful concept for introverts like us who can't tell the world what we are going through but deep down we know as zulfii bhai said "sab sambhal jaega". Jaffer's lines just approve that concept telling us from another person's perspective that sometimes we need to hear from not within us but from someone else and that truly feels like a therapy. That someone else knows what I am going through, how tangled I am, in the end we all settle somehow. It can be a fix and it might not be a fix, but it will get better.

Thank you Coke Studio for this gem, when I needed it the most ♥

snippet.textDisplay:
I don't know if you noticed but when Abdul Hannan chose the quieter street totally engrossed in his thoughts and trying to navigate his way through life , those two men who chose to walk into the buzzing street were Jaffer and Maaz - Kaavish🥹 
I loved the whole idea of it. Abdul Hannan is young, trying to figure things out, overwhelmed by thoughts just like his part of the song. On the other hand , kaavish is middle-aged, has already figured that no matter how much you overthink and analyze, life will happen the way it's supposed to happen. The only thing that matters is how you react to it. Hence 'phir tu sambhal jae ga'
Beautiful work of art . The lyrics, the composition, the singing, the set, the brilliant depiction of it all through the lens❤ coke studio Pakistan has done it once again. Take a bow!!
